    <main>
      <header>
        <h1>Nadeshiko Grind</h1>
      </header>
      <section>
        Tool to grind/shadow Japanese words & sentences using
        <a href="https://nadeshiko.co">Nadeshiko</a>
        anime examples.
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Situation</h3>
        <p>Imagine, you have tricky 🗾 words from different apps, that don't stick well in your memory.
        You save them to Anki, print them on stickers, draw them on your bathroom walls, etc. Yet it helps little.</p>
        <p>Once, a wise balding Esperanto man from YouTube told me, that sometimes you need to just grind the sentences:
        repeat the words multiple times in different context, even if it's hard. </p>
        <p>This nerdy TUI app allows you to do it. </p>
        <p>It loads words from plain text and fetches (somewhat) relevant examples from 💮, with audio and sentence decomposition,
        separately from static SRS cards. <em>Again and again.</em> That is all.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3>Usage</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Install from repo or download binary</li>
          <li>Get your words in a plain text file: export from Anki/Lute/LanguageReactor/etc, or save them into text file while you read/watch something</li>
          <li>Get API key from Nadeshiko <a href="https://nadeshiko.co/user/developer">dev page</a> (requires free registration)</li>
          <li>Launch app with the text file as an argument</li>
          <li>Go through words randomly or in original order</li>
          <li>Fetch multiple examples for each word (if there are any)</li>
          <li>If you encounter an unkown word in a sentence, you may click on it to get a new example</li>
          <li>Persist in your grind and remove the words you are fed up with from the list</li>
          <li>Speak like a person from anime and fear nothing 👺</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3>Disclaimer</h3>
